<div1 type="trialAccount" id="t18400203-780">
               <interp inst="t18400203-780" type="uri" value="sessionsPapers/18400203"></interp>
               <interp inst="t18400203-780" type="date" value="18400203"></interp>
               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t18400203-780-charge-1" targOrder="Y" targets="def1-780-18400203 t18400203-780-offence-1 t18400203-780-verdict-1"></join>
               <p>780. <persName id="def1-780-18400203" type="defendantName">
                     <interp inst="def1-780-18400203" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-780-18400203" type="age" value="23"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-780-18400203" type="surname" value="HAMMOND"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-780-18400203" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">GEORGE HAMMOND</hi>
                  </persName> was indicted<rs id="t18400203-780-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18400203-780-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="miscellaneous"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18400203-780-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="other"></interp> for a misdemeanor.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MESSRS. CHAMBERS</hi>. <hi rend="italic">and</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">SHEA</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">conducted the Prosecution.</hi>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18400203-name-1194" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18400203-name-1194" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18400203-name-1194" type="surname" value="MILLARD"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18400203-name-1194" type="given" value="ELIZABETH"></interp>ELIZABETH MILLARD</persName>
                  </hi>. I am servant to Mr. Ferguson, of Albion-ter<lb></lb>race,</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184002030182"></xptr>
               <p>Wandsworth-road, a bookseller. On the afternoon of the 23rd of Jan<lb></lb>uary the prisoner came into the shop, and asked for a Valentine—I served him with one—he put a 5<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. piece on the counter—my mistress came in and took it up—the prisoner received 4<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. in change—when he was gone my mistress showed me the crown-piece—I went out to seek for the prisoner, but could not see him—my mistress kept the 5<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. piece.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. BALLANTINE</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> It was rather early to apply for an article of that kind? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes—I had never seen him before—he had a flannel jacket on and an apron round his waist—I noticed his dress altogether—I noticed his face because he had his eyes more on the ground than on any thing else—he looked at another valentine with a rose, but that would not do because it was 1<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. SHEA</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Did he look at several? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Not a great many—I do not suppose he was there more than ten minutes—I have not the least doubt that he is the person.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18400203-name-1195" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18400203-name-1195" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18400203-name-1195" type="surname" value="FERGUSON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18400203-name-1195" type="given" value="MARY"></interp>MARY FERGUSON</persName>
                  </hi>. I am the wife of Charles Ferguson, who keeps that shop. I came into the shop while the prisoner was there—it was quite light—it was a little after three o'clock—I received the crown-piece, and gave the change—he left the shop directly, and immediately he left I dis<lb></lb>covered that the 5<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. piece was bad—I put it into my apron pocket, and kept it separate from all other money—I gave it to Emmerson the policeman on that day week—it was marked in my presence—I am certain it was the one I received from the prisoner—I had no other.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> Had you seen him before? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> No—he looked down on the floor—he did not look us in the face—he had bought the valentine before I came in—he had a hat on, and was dressed in a flannel jacket—I saw him again on the following week—I had given a description of him as having a downcast look, and I described his dress.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18400203-name-1196" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18400203-name-1196" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18400203-name-1196" type="surname" value="MILLARD"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18400203-name-1196" type="given" value="ELIZABETH"></interp>ELIZABETH MILLARD</persName>
                  </hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">re-examined</hi>. I told the policeman he was dressed in a flannel jacket, and had an apron round his waist—I did not say any thing about his having a downcast look.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18400203-name-1197" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18400203-name-1197" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18400203-name-1197" type="surname" value="EMMERSON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18400203-name-1197" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS EMMERSON</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-sergeant V</hi> 16.) Between three and four o'clock in the afternoon, on the 23rd of January, I was in Lark Hall-lane, and saw the prisoner, and a female with him, going towards London, away from the prosecutor's shop—on the 30th of January I was near the Vaux<lb></lb>hall gate, and saw the prisoner and two more persons in custody, one of whom was the female I had seen the prisoner with on the 23rd—I went with the prisoner to Mr. Ferguson's shop—I saw Mrs. Ferguson—she gave me this crown-piece—I went with the prisoner to the station-house at Clapham, and found on him 1<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>., and a new pair of braces were found in his hat, which are worth about a shilling.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> Had Mrs. Ferguson previously given you a de<lb></lb>scription of the man? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> She sent the description by another sergeant to the station-house.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">COURT</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> What description had been left? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> A young man, with a flannel jacket, and an apron, and a pencil sticking out of his pocket—the prisoner was so dressed when I saw him, and also when he was taken, and he had a pencil in his pocket, and part of it stuck out.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18400203-name-1198" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18400203-name-1198" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18400203-name-1198" type="surname" value="DITTON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18400203-name-1198" type="given" value="ELIZABETH JANE"></interp>ELIZABETH JANE DITTON</persName>
                  </hi>. I am the daughter of Benjamin Ditton, a cheesemonger, in Lambeth New-road. On the 25th of January the prisoner came and bargained for a piece of pork—I weighed the pork—it came to 2<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.—I told him so and he threw down a half-crown—on taking it up I</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184002030183"></xptr>
               <p>said it was a bad one—he said he did not know it, and he held his hand out for me to give it him back—I told him to go about hit business, and he went directly—I put the half-crown behind me on the cheeses—I kept it separate till the 30th of January, and then gave it to the policeman—I am sure it was the same that I received from the prisoner—he was in the shop about three minutes—it was between seven and eight o'clock in the evening—I had a distinct sight of him, so as to know him again—I am certain he is the man.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18400203-name-1199" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18400203-name-1199" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18400203-name-1199" type="surname" value="LAING"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18400203-name-1199" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN LAING</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable N</hi> 70.) In consequence of information I went to Mr. Ditton's shop, on the 30th of January, and received this half-crown from Miss Ditton—on the next morning I had the prisoner and two more persons in custody—I took them to Mr. Ditton's shop, and Miss Ditton identified the prisoner.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner</hi>. She said she was not sure I was the person. <hi rend="italic">Witness</hi>. No—she said the man in the flannel jacket was the man.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18400203-name-1200" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18400203-name-1200" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18400203-name-1200" type="surname" value="FIELD"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18400203-name-1200" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>MR. JOHN FIELD</persName>
                  </hi>. I am inspector of coin to the Royal Mint. These are both counterfeit.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="largeCaps">
                     <rs id="t18400203-780-verdict-1" type="verdictDescription">
                        <interp inst="t18400203-780-verdict-1" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18400203-780-verdict-1" type="verdictSubcategory" value="no_subcategory"></interp>GUILTY</rs>
                  </hi>. Aged 23.—
